<article class="container strategy">
  <div class="row">
    <header>
      <h1>The Knot UX Strategy</h1>
    </header>

    <hr>

    <section>
      <h3>Background</h3>
      <p>
        The Knot was launched in to the Australian market in October 2009, off the back of the very successful website and magazine of the same name in the US. In Australia, The Knot creates revenue through ad placements (managed by NineMSN) and suppliers paying for listings (see Business Value Model below). Since 2009 the site has grown in complexity leading to a disjointed user experience for its primary users (visitors, suppliers and admins). The Knot therefore wants to revise the site's overall experience in order to drive more value to all site users.
      </p>
      <hr>
      <h4>The Knot Business Value Model</h4>
      <img src="/images/business_value.jpg">
    </section>

    <hr>

    <ul class="nav nav-tabs">
      <li class="active">
        <a href="#business-strategy">Business</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#visitor-strategy">Visitor</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#supplier-strategy">Supplier</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#admin-strategy">Admin</a>
      </li>
      <li>
        <a href="#must-haves-strategy">Must haves</a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="tab-content">
      <div id="business-strategy" class="tab-pane active">
        <%= erb :ux_strategy_busines %>
      </div>

      <div id="visitor-strategy" class="tab-pane">
        <%= erb :ux_strategy_visitor %>
      </div>

      <div id="supplier-strategy" class="tab-pane">
        <%= erb :ux_strategy_supplier %>
      </div>

      <div id="admin-strategy" class="tab-pane">
        <%= erb :ux_strategy_admin %>
      </div>

      <div id="must-haves-strategy" class="tab-pane">
        <section>
          <h3>Must haves</h3>
          <ul>
            <li><b>Interoperability:</b> desktop, mobile, tablet</li>
            <li><b>Speed: </b>median page load @ 1.5s (currently 7,2 s), median 95th percentile page load @ 3s.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
        <hr>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>